formanceRow`, `PeekGrowthClaimRow`\n1125\t    (extends per-user `PeekReferralClaimRow` with `userId`, `username`,\n1126\t    `wallet` so the table can link rows back to user-detail),\n1127\t    `PeekReferralClaimFilters`, `PeekReferralGraphRefereeRow`,\n1128\t    `PeekReferralGraphInboundReferrer`, `PeekReferralGraphNode`. All\n1129\t    browser-safe; no server imports introduced.\n1130\t- Boundedness + safety:\n1131\t  - Every list query takes a `limit` and clamps it through `clampLimit`\n1132\t    against per-feature `DEFAULT` and `MAX` constants exported from the\n1133\t    module (`PEEK_GROWTH_TOP_REFERRERS_DEFAULT_LIMIT`,\n1134\t    `PEEK_GROWTH_KOL_DEFAULT_LIMIT`,\n1135\t    `PEEK_GROWTH_CLAIMS_DEFAULT_LIMIT`).\n1136\t  - `Promise.all` parallelises the eight overview counts so the metrics\n1137\t    page does not chain queries sequentially.\n1138\t  - Filters are passed as parameterised values (no `unsafe`); `null`\n1139\t    filters are skipped via `(${condition === null} or …)` template\n1140\t    expressions matching the existing `list-peek-users.ts` pattern.\n1141\t- No frontend wiring this iteration — the next two checklist items\n1142\t  (`/growth/referrals` + `/growth/kol` UI, then dedicated tests) handle\n1143\t  page composition and assertion coverage.\n1144\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n1145\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (196/196, no regressions).\n1146\t## Iteration 27 — 2026-04-25T12:22:12Z — OK\n1147\t- **Log**: iteration-027.log\n1148\t\n1149\t## Iteration 28 — 2026-04-25\n1150\t\n1151\t- FR-7 frontend pages: wired the growth/referral and growth/kol surfaces on\n1152\t  top of iteration 27's queries.\n1153\t  - `peek/app/growth/referrals/page.tsx` — server-rendered route. Loads the\n1154\t    8-metric overview into `MetricStrip`, the top-50 referrer table, and a\n1155\t    URL-addressable claims table. Each section has its own try/catch so a\n1156\t    single broken query doesn't blank the page; errors render through the\n1157\